    <%= render 'sidebar' %>

    <div class="col-md-8 text-justify">
      <h1 style="font-size: 4em;">Make Your Own App</h1>

      <p class="lead">Once the prototype of Wild Plant ID app has been coded, field tested, debugged
      and released to the public it will be converted into a template app which can be
      used by other organizations and individuals to create Wild Plant ID for their area.</p>
      <p>Steps to create a Wild Plant ID app for your area...</p>

      <ol>
        <li>Become an app curator.</li>
        	<p>
      	  Register with Wild Plant ID as an app curator and delineate the area you will
      	  be creating the app for. We reccommend that your area be one with natural boundaries
      	  such as a watershed, but other boundaries are acceptable such as a park or conservation area.
        	</p>
        <li>Create a list of plants for your area.</li>

      <ol type="A">
      	<li>Locate any existing plants lists for your area.</li>
      	<li>Research local herbarium.</li>
      	<li>Check online resources, such as BONAP (Biota of North America Program) at <a href="http://www.bonap.org">www.bonap.org</a>.</li>
      </ol>

        <li>Acquire photos of plants not already in Wild Plant ID database.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
</div>

